canonical:
  title: 謝元戎李密直來訪
  author: 卓光茂
  language: lzh
  text: 明君憂閫外授鉞遣雄才深策海難測嚴威山可摧箭飛紛似雨劒擊迅如雷掃蕩妖氛盡扶持化日回元功歸帶礪碩輔待塩梅豈謂高軒貴親探陋巷來紫駞峯出釜綠蟻酒盈杯席上綺羅擁罇前絃管催千愁割爾散一笑粲然開糜粉亦何報兢惶不自裁
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 謝元戎李密直來訪
  author: 卓光茂
  language: lzh
  text: 明君憂閫外。授鉞遣雄才。深策海難測。嚴威山可摧。箭飛紛似雨。劒擊迅如雷。掃蕩妖氛盡。扶持化日回。元功歸帶礪。碩輔待塩梅。豈謂高軒貴。親探陋巷來。紫駞峯出釜。綠蟻酒盈杯。席上綺羅擁。罇前絃管催。千愁割爾散。一笑粲然開。糜粉亦何報。兢惶不自裁。
korean:
  title: 원융 이밀직이 찾아왔음을 감사하며
  author: 탁광무
  language: kor
  text: |-
    명군께서 곤외 일을 근심하시와
    웅재에게 월을 내려 주시니
    깊은 그 획책은 바다와 같고
    엄한 그 위엄은 산도 꺾을 만
    화살이 빗발 치듯 날고
    검은 번개처럼 빨리 휘둘러
    요분을 모조리 쓸어 버리니
    어와, 태평 일월 돌아오누나
    버젓이 대려의 큰 공을 세워
    고대 염매로써 정승 되리니
    놀라와라, 저렇듯 고귀한 분이
    몸소 이런 누항에 찾아오다니
    솥에선 자타봉(낙타의 등살. 진미라 한다.) 등살 나오고
    잔에는 녹의 뜬 술이 넘치네
    좌상에 비단 옷 입은 기생들이 옹위했고
    술상 앞엔 관현 소리 징징 늴리리
    천 가지 시름이 확 풀어지고
    한바탕 웃음이 “하하” 터지네
    뼈가 가루 된들 이 은혜 어이 갚으리
    송구한 마음을 가눌 길 없네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0140_010_0310&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 곤외(閫外) : '
    value: 옛날에 임금이 대장(大將)을 밖으로 출병하여 보낼 적에 그의 탄 수레바퀴를 손으로 밀어주며, “문턱 안에 일은 내가 맡고 문턱 밖에 일은 장군이 맡아서 처리하라.” 하였다.
english:
  title: Thanking Won Yung and Yi Mil-jik for Their Visit
  author: Tak Gwang-mu
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The enlightened ruler grieves for the realm beyond the gates,
    Entrusting his generals with command and sacred trust.
    Their deep strategies run as fathomless as the sea,
    Their stern authority can topple mountains bare.

    Arrows fly thick as rain in torrents,
    Swords strike swift as thunder's crack.
    The demon-mists are swept entirely clean,
    And lo—the days of peace return once more.

    Vast merit stands recorded in the annals grand,
    Waiting the wise minister fit as salt and plum.
    Yet here—this honored, exalted lord
    Comes himself to this humble, narrow lane!

    From the cauldron rises camel's hump delicacy,
    In the cup, green-frothed wine brims over.
    Round the table, silken-robed beauties gather close,
    Before us, strings and wind-pipes call and sing.

    A thousand cares dissolve and scatter,
    Laughter bursts forth in bright cascade.
    Though flesh turn to powder and bone to dust,
    How could I ever repay such grace?
    My heart trembles—I know not how to bear it.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The phrase 'beyond the gates' (곤외) refers to the realm of military command outside the palace, where generals hold autonomous authority to defend the state.
  - key: ''
    value: Salt and plum (塩梅) is a classical metaphor for the ideal complementary relationship between a ruler and his ministers, derived from how these seasonings balance a dish.
  - key: ''
    value: The camel's hump was considered a delicacy in East Asian cuisine, symbolizing the host's respect and generosity toward honored guests.
